                <fr:route>/schm-5YJS/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Quasi-compact morphisms are closed under pullback">Quasi-compact morphisms are closed under pullback</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X \to  Y]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/schm-BH0E/" title="Quasi-compact morphisms" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-BH0E/" display-uri="schm-BH0E" type="local">quasi-compact</fr:link> between schemes, then so is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Z \times _Y X \to  Z]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g : Z \to  Y]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> is an affine open in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Z]]></fr:tex>. For any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\in  g[U]]]></fr:tex>, choose an affine open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V_y]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{g^{-1}(V_y)\}_{y\in  g[U]}]]></fr:tex> covers <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex>, which means there will be a finite subcover since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> is compact. This way, since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is quasi-compact, each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}(V_y)]]></fr:tex> is covered by finitely many affine opens <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigcup _{j_y}U_{j_y}]]></fr:tex>, which implies
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[ (g^*f)^{-1}(U) \subseteq  U \times  \bigcup _{y,j_y}U_{j_y}, ]]></fr:tex>
  is a finite union of affine opens, hence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g^*f]]></fr:tex> is quasi-compact as well.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
